11.2 Neither party waives any rights they might have, but either party retains the discretionary power to promptly terminate this agreement by written notice, without prior notice, should they deem it necessary, for whatever reason, or upon occurrence of the following events:

a) Material breach by the other party of any terms and conditions stated in this agreement;
b) Insolvency, bankruptcy, receivership, or liquidation proceedings initiated by or against either party;
c) A change in law or regulatory requirement that significantly affects the ability of a party to perform its obligations under this agreement.

This revised clause provides both parties with the option to terminate the agreement at their discretion, without prior notice, for any reason (including material breach), and also covers instances of insolvency or significant changes in law affecting either party's ability to fulfill obligations.
